==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corselet
<hw>Corse"let</hw> <pr>(k?rs"l?t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., dim. of
OF. <ets>cors</ets>. F. <ets>corps</ets>, body. See
<er>Corse</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Armor for the body, as, the body
breastplate and backpiece taken together; -- also, used for the entire
suit of the day, including breastplate and backpiece, tasset and
headpiece.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The thorax of an
insect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corsepresent</ent>⟦br⟧
